Rating: 4
This has been our little family's standard waffle recipe (minus prosciutto) for our seven years of marriage and is much loved. We have reduced the butter over the years, we make a quadruple recipe and put in 2 sticks of butter, so we reduce the butter to 4T per recipe. We make it in a standard four square waffle iron, about 1/4 cup of batter per square. Delicious fresh, and the extras go into the freezer and are rewarmed in the toaster oven at 350 for 6-8 minutes.

