Rating: 3
We made this recipe (minus the prosciutto) for our kid's Mickey Mouse waffle maker. The batter made about 3-4 waffles. Considering the amount of butter we cut back to 3T - and it still makes for more than 15g of fat per waffle. While delicious, they are not everyday waffles!

Rating: 3
We used this recipe (minus the proscuitto) for the kids' Mickey Mouse waffle maker. It made about 3-4 waffles this way, and with 5T of butter... well that's a lot of fat per waffle! We cut the butter back to 3T and still it is 15 grams of fat per waffle. While delicious, it's not an everyday recipe!

Rating: 4
Is the prosciutto non-essential or did people a. Did not want to spent the 16 bucks a pound or b. Did not get any and just said the hell with it.. hmmm. Great basic waffle recipe, prosciutto adds a smokiness and an elegance that could warrant a sunday brunch and some mimosas. If you want a pronounced buttermilk flavor then add artificial buttermilk flavoring like Mcdonald's does.

Rating: 3
I have been trying to come up with a waffle recipe that will please everyone in my family (2 boys and husband). I think this one is it. My kids loved them, and my husband said several times that they were "awesome." I added 1 teaspoon of sugar and 1/2 teaspoon of vanilla. Did not serve with the prosciutto. The boys poured Mrs. Butterworth on them. They were big, fat, sweet waffles.

